LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF IDAHO
Sixty-eighth Legislature First Regular Session - 2025
IN THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
HOUSE BILL NO. 462
BY REVENUE AND TAXATION COMMITTEE
1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO TAXATION; AMENDING SECTION 63-3022I, IDAHO CODE, TO PROVIDE FOR
3 THE DEDUCTION OF CERTAIN FEES, COSTS, AND EXPENSES RELATED TO EMBRYOS;
4 AND DECLARING AN EMERGENCY AND PROVIDING RETROACTIVE APPLICATION.
5 Be It Enacted by the Legislature of the State of Idaho:
6 SECTION 1. That Section 63-3022I, Idaho Code, be, and the same is hereby
7 amended to read as follows:
8 63-3022I. ADOPTION AND EMBRYO EXPENSES. For taxable years commencing
9 on or after January 1, 2018, legal fees and costs and medical expenses and
10 costs all related to the adoption of a child may be deducted from taxable
11 income by adoptive parents. The deduction allowed pursuant to this section
12 shall not exceed ten thousand dollars ($10,000) for the legal fees and costs
13 and medical expenses and costs incurred in the adoption, or the actual costs
14 of the legal fees and costs and medical expenses and costs incurred in the
15 adoption, whichever amount is less, which amount may not include travel
16 costs. The deduction allowed pursuant to this section shall also apply to
17 legal fees and medical expenses related to the acquisition and transfer into
18 the human body of a donated embryo that results in a live birth; in such case,
19 the deduction shall be taken in the tax year that the live birth occurs and
20 any legal fees and medical expenses related to the acquisition and transfer
21 of the donated embryo for the three (3) years immediately preceding the live
22 birth may be deducted.
23 SECTION 2. An emergency existing therefor, which emergency is hereby
24 declared to exist, this act shall be in full force and effect on and after its
25 passage and approval, and retroactively to January 1, 2025.

